{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "The smart home generates a continuous stream of raw sensor data that is pre-processed by the Sensor State Generation module to obtain a stream of sensor states.",
    "Intuitively, a sensor state represents the timespan in which a sensor is active (e.g., \"the TV in the living room is ON from 12:34 to 13:02'').",
    "Then, the stream of sensor states is segmented in fixed-time windows by the Segmentation module.Since LLMs are specialized in natural language text, the main idea of ADL-LLM is to generate a natural language representation for each window, so that an LLM can \"reason\" on it leveraging its implicit common-sense knowledge.",
    "The Window2Text module is in charge of transforming windows of sensor states into natural language sentences describing what happened in the home during that window.",
    "The LLM receives as input a System Prompt (i.e., instructions about the task it has to perform) and a User Prompt (i.e., the textual representation of the window enriched with additional instructions for the LLM by the User Prompt Construction module)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}